-- Capitals Beat Rangers in Overtime for 2-0 Lead in NHL Playoffs
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-04T19:52:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-04/capitals-beat-rangers-in-overtime-for-2-0-lead-in-nhl-playoffs.html
The  Washington Capitals  beat the New
York Rangers 1-0 in overtime to take a two-games-to-none lead in
their National Hockey League playoff series.  Mike Green scored a power-play goal eight minutes into
overtime at the Verizon Center in  Washington . The score came
with New York’s Ryan McDonagh serving a delay-of-game penalty
for shooting the puck over the glass.  New York goaltender Henrik Lundqvist made 37 saves, while
Washington’s Braden Holtby stopped 24 shots.  Game 3 of the best-of-seven Eastern Conference series will
be played at New York’s Madison Square Garden in two days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  